.TH "sock_create_lite" 9 "sock_create_lite" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sock_create_lite \- creates a socket
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sock_create_lite
.BI "(int family "  ","
.BI "int type "  ","
.BI "int protocol "  ","
.BI "struct socket **res "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "family" 12
protocol family (AF_INET, ...)
.IP "type" 12
communication type (SOCK_STREAM, ...)
.IP "protocol" 12
protocol (0, ...)
.IP "res" 12
new socket

Creates a new socket and assigns it to \fIres\fP, passing through LSM.
The new socket initialization is not complete, see \fBkernel_accept\fP.
Returns 0 or an error. On failure \fIres\fP is set to NULL.
This function internally uses GFP_KERNEL.
